      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The escrow account is typically managed by the title company or a specialized escrow agent, who acts as a neutral third party to hold the funds. They're usually bonded and insured to protect the funds, so you can be confident that they're safe. The money is usually held in a separate account, not a vault, and is kept separate from the title company's regular accounts to ensure its security. The escrow agent will disburse the funds according to the terms of the sale, such as paying property taxes and insurance when they become due. You can even request a statement of account to verify the funds are being held and managed correctly.",
